resposta: The Eastern Front of World War I was a major theater of operations during the war  stretching from Eastern Europe to the Russian Far East. It involved many of the world's great powers  including Germany  Russia  Austria-Hungary  Great Britain  and the United States  as well as smaller nations such as Romania  Bulgaria  and Ottoman Turkey. The front was marked by numerous battles and campaigns  including the Brusilov Offensive  the Battle of Stalingrad  and the Siege of Leningrad. It is widely considered to be one of the bloodiest and most devastating conflicts in history  with millions of casualties.
